Last Broadcast Date: Tue 23 Sep 2014
Natalio Cosoy of BBC Mundo, reports on his 30-something generation growing up in the shadow of the violence of military rule in the 1970s and 1980s. He talks to musicians, friends and the half-brothers whose left-wing militant parents were killed by the military. It is a story of survival and the music that helped them and the country forge a new Argentine identity. Show less